{% extends 'document.njk' %}

{% set document = {
  description: 'A collection of logos, optimized to be rendered at 24x24*',
  isHome: true,
  slug: 'home'
} %}

{% block content %}
  <main class="main">
    <section class="main__section">
      <div class="main__inner">
        <div class="main__container">
          <h1 class="heading heading_first">
            A collection of logos,
            <br>
            optimized to be rendered at 24x24*
          </h1>
          <a
            class="button button_mb"
            href="https://board.svg24.dev/"
          >
            Open collection
          </a>
          <p class="description description_first description_sm">
            Requires the
            <a class="link" href="https://github.com/browserslist/browserslist">latest browser's</a>
            versions. Absolutely free.
          </p>
        </div>
        <img
          alt="Board preview"
          class="main__preview"
          src="/assets/images/board-preview.webp"
        >
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="main__section main__section_colored">
      <div class="main__inner">
        <h2 class="heading heading_second">
          Optimization
        </h2>
        <p class="description description_first">
          The first step is to optimize the logo using SVGO â€” this is necessary
          in order to make the subsequent manual work more comfortable.
          The next step is manual optimization in the vector editor
          of what was not processed in the previous step. And finally,
          the logo once again optimize using SVGO with more gentle plugins.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="main__section">
      <div class="main__inner">
        <h2 class="heading heading_second">
          Types
        </h2>
        <p class="description description_first">
          For convenience, in the collection,
          each logo is presented in two types.
        </p>
        <div class="main__columns">
          {% set types = [{
            name: 'Original',
            image: 'original',
            description: 'The logo retains its original width, height is 24 units, padding is 2.'
          }, {
            name: '24x24',
            image: '24x24',
            description: 'Width as well as height is 24 units, padding is 2.'
          }] %}
          {% for item in types %}
            <div class="main__column">
              <h3 class="heading heading_third">
                {{ item.name }}
              </h3>
              <img
                class="main__type"
                src="/assets/images/type-{{ item.image }}.webp"
              >
              <p class="description description_second">
                {{ item.description }}
              </p>
            </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="main__section main__section_colored">
      <div class="main__inner">
        <h2 class="heading heading_second">
          Are you a designer? Developer?
          <br>
          It does not matter
        </h2>
        <p class="description description_first description_mb">
          Logos available as files, snippets and frameworks components.
        </p>
        <a
          class="button"
          href="https://board.svg24.dev/"
        >
          Open collection
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
{% endblock %}
